						<b>Andong Shikhye (fermented rice punch, Andong style) </b><br><br>
						Glutinous rice is steamed and radish and pear are thin-sliced as flat square or strips. These are mixed in malt water that is tinted with powdered red pepper water and fermented. The characteristic of this shikhye is that it is not boiled and has sharply pungent taste.
						</td>
